3ï¸âƒ£ Main Components

ğŸ”¹ Frontend Layer

Tech: React / Angular
Features:
Upload Resume (PDF/DOC).
Paste Job Description text.
Show Match Score (0â€“100%), missing skills, suggestions.
Dashboard for recruiters (upload multiple resumes).

ğŸ”¹ Backend Layer (Spring Boot â€“ Java)

Acts as API Gateway.
Responsibilities:
Handle requests (resume upload, JD submission).
Store & retrieve metadata from DB.
Communicate with ML microservice via REST API.
Manage authentication (JWT, OAuth).

ğŸ”¹ ML Microservice (Python + FastAPI/Flask)

Independent service for AI/NLP tasks.
Responsibilities:
Parse resumes (extract text using PyMuPDF/pdfminer).
Extract job skills using NER (spaCy/HuggingFace).
Generate embeddings (SBERT / Sentence Transformers).
Compute similarity (cosine similarity).
Identify missing keywords/skills.

ğŸ”¹ AI/NLP Engine

Models Used:
Resume & JD Embeddings â†’ Sentence-BERT.
Named Entity Recognition (NER) â†’ spaCy (for extracting skills, education, companies).

Logic:
Vectorize Resume & JD.
Compare similarity.
Suggest missing skills.

ğŸ”¹ Database Layer

PostgreSQL (structured data) or MongoDB (if storing JSON resumes).

Tables/Collections:
users â†’ user info.
resumes â†’ resume metadata + S3 link.
job_descriptions â†’ JD text.
match_results â†’ scores, missing skills, timestamp.

ğŸ”¹ Cloud Infrastructure

AWS (example):
S3 â†’ Store resumes securely.
EC2 / Elastic Beanstalk â†’ Host Spring Boot backend.
Lambda / EC2 â†’ Run ML microservice.
RDS â†’ PostgreSQL DB.
CloudWatch â†’ Monitoring & logs.
